RDNA4 fix: enable triton (flash) attention for NemotronH Mamba2-hybrid models.

TritonAttnBackend.__init__ samples the value head dim via get_value_buffer(0) on
the KV pool. For a Mamba2-Transformer hybrid the full-attention layers live at
sparse indices (NemotronH-Nano-Omni: [5,12,19,26,33,42]) and layer 0 is a Mamba
layer with NO entry in the HybridLinearKVPool's full_attention_layer_id_mapping,
so get_value_buffer(0) raises:
  ValueError: layer_id=0 not in full attention layers: dict_keys([5,12,19,26,33,42])
and triton attention can't initialize -> the model was stuck on torch_native,
whose only available SDPA backend on ROCm is MATH (flash/mem-efficient report
"No available kernel"), which materializes O(chunk x context) scores and OOMs
past ~150K. The backend already special-cases hybrid_gdn_config / kimi_linear /
linear_attn_model_spec to call get_v_head_dim() instead, but those miss the
Nano-Omni config class (loaded via trust-remote-code; mamba2_config doesn't
recognize it). Fix: also duck-type on the pool -- any HybridLinearKVPool exposes
get_v_head_dim() (samples the full_kv_pool's first full-attention layer), so use
it whenever present. With triton flash attention the model serves full 256K
memory-efficiently (247K-tok prefill, full-token-usage 0.07, ~109s, ~29 tok/s
decode) with default mem-fraction/chunked-prefill. Pure-additive condition; CUDA
and non-hybrid pools (MHATokenToKVPool, no get_v_head_dim) are unaffected.

